The paper deals with the definability of the reachability relation in timed automata, which is a topic in logic and automata theory. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves linear arithmetic, which is a topic in programming languages and formal methods, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves the study of the structure of timed automata, which is a topic in discrete mathematics and graph theory, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the study of time complexity, which is a topic in theoretical computer science, making cs.LT (Theoretical Computer Science) a possible sub-category.
